{
  "texts": [
    "In each panel, the dash-dotted line indicates the median of the ∆ log(τ DRW) distribution, and the shaded region shows its central 68% interval.",
    "The top, middle, and bottom panels correspond to three common point estimators: MLE, MCMC posterior median, and MCMC posterior mean, respectively.",
    "Among these, the MCMC posterior median is the most robust, remaining systematically unbiased as long as the the recovered τ DRW is less than one-tenth of the baseline (dash-dotted lines in the middle panel of Figure 9).",
    "It introduces only a small systematic bias (∼ 0.1 dex) when the recovered τ DRW is about one-third of the baseline.",
    "In this work, we assume that AGN stochastic variability follows a DRW process; however, the modeling framework introduced here is sufficiently flexible to accommodate alternative GP kernels for characterizing the underlying variability."
  ]
}